## Coding Guidelines

### General
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Keep components simple and focused
- Avoid over-engineering solutions
- No unnecessary abstractions
- Mobile-first responsive design

### Styling
- ALWAYS use CSS custom properties from `app.css`
- Use `var(--color-*)` for all colors
- Use `var(--gradient-purple*)` for gradients
- Use `var(--button-glow*)` for shadow effects
- Maintain consistent spacing (0.75rem, 1rem, 1.25rem increments)
- Border radius: 8px for small elements, 12px for cards

### Responsive Design
- Desktop-first in hero, then adapt for mobile
- Key breakpoint: `@media (max-width: 768px)`
- Use `dvh` for dynamic viewport height on mobile
- Reduce font sizes and padding on mobile

### Component Patterns
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  export let propName: type = defaultValue;
</script>

<div class="component-name">
  <!-- content -->
</div>

<style>
  .component-name {
    /* styles using CSS custom properties */
  }
</style>
```

## Don't Do This
- Don't create new color schemes - use existing CSS variables
- Don't add unnecessary files or documentation unless requested
- Don't over-engineer simple features
- Don't use emojis unless explicitly requested
- Don't add comments for self-evident code
- Don't create abstractions for one-time use

